<h2 id="9.-Clustering">9. Clustering<a class="anchor-link" href="#9.-Clustering">&#182;</a></h2>

<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="prompt input_prompt">

<div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<p>The starter code can be found in k_means/k_means_cluster.py, which reads in the email + financial (E+F) dataset and gets us ready for clustering. You'll start with performing k-means based on just two financial features--take a look at the code, and determine which features the code uses for clustering.</p>
<p>Run the code, which will create a scatterplot of the data. Think a little bit about what clusters you would expect to arise if 2 clusters are created.</p>
